00:15:45.343 --> 00:15:47.579
Um, but it was
kind of a conspiracy theory,

00:15:47.612 --> 00:15:49.181
because it was a suspicion.

00:15:49.214 --> 00:15:51.316
And that distance

00:15:51.349 --> 00:15:53.919
between suspicion and fact

00:15:53.952 --> 00:15:55.854
is everything in a democracy.

00:15:55.887 --> 00:15:58.390
That is all we have
in a free society, because we--

00:15:58.423 --> 00:16:02.060
if we can't agree
on what is happening,

00:16:02.093 --> 00:16:03.862
how can we decide

00:16:03.895 --> 00:16:06.431
what we should do about it?

00:16:06.464 --> 00:16:09.034
Government in a democracy
derives its, uh,

00:16:09.067 --> 00:16:11.570
legitimacy from the consent
of the governed.

00:16:11.603 --> 00:16:14.106
And the biggest problem in 2013,

00:16:14.139 --> 00:16:18.043
uh, was that consent is only
meaningful if it's informed.

00:16:18.076 --> 00:16:19.778
And they lied to us.

00:16:19.811 --> 00:16:23.048
Edward Snowden, thank you so
much for joining us on the show.

